## Stack

- Echo with Huma-generated OpenAPI 3.1 and interactive docs.
- sqlc and Goose using {{.Database}}.
- Feature-local domain, application, HTTP adapter, and repository adapter modules.
- Zap-ready structured logging, typed errors, cursor pagination, RBAC, jobs, and rate-limit seams.
{{if .Auth}}- Secure cookie authentication and multi-tenant authorization are selected.{{end}}
- {{if .Frontend}}React, Vite, TanStack Router/Query, Tailwind, Zustand, and hey-api.{{else}}Backend-only project; a frontend can be added later.{{end}}{{if and .Frontend (not .Auth)}}
  Authentication screens are examples only because auth was not selected.{{end}}

## Repository Map

```text
backend/   Go API, workers, migrations, queries, and feature modules
frontend/  React application and generated OpenAPI client
docs/      Architecture and feature authoring guides
```

Within `backend/internal/features/<feature>`, domain code points inward and owns repository interfaces; application behavior depends on those interfaces; HTTP and sqlc packages are adapters. Only `internal/bootstrap` constructs process-lifetime dependencies.

## Start {{.Database}}

```sh
cd backend
docker compose up -d db
```

Copy `backend/.env.example` to `backend/.env` and adjust credentials when needed.

## Run the complete local demo

```sh
make demo
```

This creates `backend/.env` from the example when it is absent, starts the database, regenerates sqlc output, migrates, applies the idempotent `demo` seed, and runs the API{{if .Jobs}}, worker{{end}}{{if .Cron}}, scheduler{{end}}{{if .Frontend}}, and frontend{{end}}. Press `Ctrl+C` to stop application processes; the database volume remains available for the next run.

The API address comes from `backend/.env` (`HTTP_ADDRESS`, default `:8080`). Override ports without changing generated files when a local port is unavailable:

```sh
HTTP_ADDRESS=:18080 VITE_API_PROXY_TARGET=http://localhost:18080 VITE_PORT=5174 make demo
```

{{if .Frontend}}The frontend opens at `http://127.0.0.1:$VITE_PORT` (default `5173`) and sends `/api` requests to `VITE_API_PROXY_TARGET`; Swagger is at `http://localhost$HTTP_ADDRESS/docs`.{{else}}Swagger is at `http://localhost$HTTP_ADDRESS/docs`.{{end}}

## Run the backend with Air

```sh
cd backend
air
```

Without Air:

```sh
cd backend
go run ./cmd/api
```

OpenAPI is served at `http://localhost:8080/openapi.json` and docs at `http://localhost:8080/docs`.

## Run migrations and seeds

```sh
cd backend
go run ./cmd/migrate up
go run ./cmd/seed --profile {{.Seed}}
```

{{if .Auth}}## Local demo sign-in

Running either the `minimal` or `demo` seed profile creates this **development-only** owner account for `Demo Organization`:

```text
Email:    owner@example.test
Password: DemoPass123!
```

The seed writes the password as a bcrypt hash and is idempotent. Do not use these public credentials outside local development; use the `none` profile and create an account through the sign-up screen for non-demo environments.
{{end}}

